#: ../docs/devices/device_mgmt/requests.rst:55
msgid "Once a request has been initiated, an MQTT message will be published to all devices specified in the request body. For each device, a response must be sent back indicating whether or not the reboot action can be initiated. If this operation can be initiated immediately, set ``rc`` to ``202``. If the reboot attempt fails, set ``rc`` to ``500`` and set the ``message`` field accordingly. If reboot is not supported, set ``rc`` to ``501`` and optionally set the ``message`` field accordingly."
